entry.def: A rating of something is a score or measurement of how good or popular it is.

example.ex: ...a value-for-money rating of ten out of ten...
New public opinion polls show the president's approval rating at its lowest point since he took office.
example.tran: 新的民意调查显示总统的支持率跌到了他就职以来的最低点。

entry.def: The ratings are the statistics published each week which show how popular each television programme is.

example.ex: Eurocops was beaten in the ratings on Channel 4 by Kate and Allie, Hill Street Blues and St Elsewhere...
example.tran: 在第4频道的收视率调查中《欧洲警察》被《凯特和阿莉》、《希尔街的布鲁斯》和《何方神圣》打败。

example.ex: CBS's ratings again showed huge improvement over the previous year.
example.tran: 与前一年相比，哥伦比亚广播公司的收视率再次大幅提高。

entry.def: Ratings are the sailors in some national navies who are not officers or who have no rank.
